# [C-09] Build-context policy for `docker build` (context = repo root).
#
# The previous policy was an ALLOWLIST — `*` (ignore everything) plus three
# `!docker/...` re-includes. That excluded package.json, package-lock.json AND
# the entire app/ source tree, so the Dockerfile's `COPY package.json
# package-lock.json ./` and `COPY . .` copied nothing: `npm ci` and
# `npx gulp deploy` had no inputs and the image could not build at all.
#
# This is a DENYLIST instead: everything is sent to the build context EXCEPT the
# heavy or regenerated artifacts listed below. The build needs the manifests, the
# full app/ source, gulpfile.js, tsconfig.json, conf.example.json and the docker/
# helper files — all of which are now included by default.

# Dependencies are reinstalled deterministically from the lockfile by `npm ci`.
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build output is regenerated by `npx gulp deploy` inside the image.
dist

# VCS metadata/history — large and never read by `npm ci` or `gulp deploy`
# (npm git-deps are fetched from GitHub over the network, not from local .git).
.git
.gitignore
.gitmodules

# Committed e2e visual-evidence deliverable (screenshots/recordings) — large and
# never consumed by the build; keep it out of the daemon build context.
e2e-react/artifacts

# Test/coverage caches and editor/OS cruft.
coverage
.nyc_output
.cache
*.log
npm-debug.log*
.DS_Store

# CI configuration is not needed to build the image.
.github
